[[!meta title="Numerous security holes in T(A)ILS 0.6"]]
[[!pagetemplate template="news.tmpl"]]

[[!tag security/fixed]]

The following security holes affect T(A)ILS 0.6.

We **strongly** urge you to [[upgrade to T(A)ILS
0.6.1|news/version_0.6.1]] in case you are still using an older version.

  - Tor (DSA-2136-1)
  - Iceweasel libraries: xulrunner (DSA-2124, DSA-2132), NSS (DSA-2123)
  - Linux kernel (DSA-2126)
  - OpenSSL (DSA-2125)
  - Glibc (DSA-2122)
  - bind9 (DSA-2130)
  - libxml2 (DSA-2128)

These are Debian security announces; details can be found on
<http://security.debian.org/>.
